  "text": "## Java ClassLoader Delegation Chain in OpenJDK\n\nThe Java ClassLoader delegation chain is implemented across multiple layers in OpenJDK:\n\n### 1. Core Java API Layer (java.lang.ClassLoader)\nFile: `src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java`\n\nThe `loadClass(String, boolean)` method (lines 534-570) implements the fundamental parent-first delegation model:\n- First checks if a class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass()`\n- If not cached and parent exists, delegates to `parent.loadClass()`\n- If no parent (at bootstrap), calls `findBootstrapClassOrNull()` to check bootstrap classes\n- If still not found, invokes `findClass()` to load the class\n- Optionally resolves the class if the `resolve` parameter is true\n- Uses `getClassLoadingLock()` for thread-safe loading\n\n### 2. Built-in ClassLoader Infrastructure (jdk.internal.loader)\n\n#### BuiltinClassLoader\nFile: `src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java`\n\nExtends `SecureClassLoader` and forms the base for all three built-in loaders. Key features:\n- Implements a module-aware delegation model that allows platform loader to delegate to app loader\n- Manages module loading via `loadModule()` method\n- Supports loading from URL class paths\n- Maintains a map of package names to loaded modules\n- Registered as parallel capable for concurrent class loading\n\n#### ClassLoaders Factory\nFile: `src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java`\n\nCreates and manages the three built-in loaders (lines 62-99):\n\n1. **BootClassLoader** (lines 131-140): \n   - Parent: `null`\n   - Loads core JDK classes from bootstrap classpath\n   - Extends BuiltinClassLoader\n\n2. **PlatformClassLoader** (lines 146-155):\n   - Parent: BootClassLoader\n   - Loads Java SE platform APIs and JDK implementation classes\n   - Extends BuiltinClassLoader\n\n3. **AppClassLoader** (lines 161-187):\n   - Parent: PlatformClassLoader\n   - Loads user application classes from the application classpath\n   - Extends BuiltinClassLoader\n   - Supports dynamic instrumentation via `appendToClassPathForInstrumentation()`\n\n#### BootLoader Utility\nFile: `src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BootLoader.java`\n\nProvides a restricted API for accessing the boot class loader's unnamed module and service catalog. Manages native libraries and module resources for the boot loader.\n\n### 3. HotSpot Native Implementation\n\n#### Class Loading Engine\nFile: `src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp`\n\nImplements native class loading operations in C++:\n- Handles bootstrap classpath parsing and initialization\n- Loads classes using the jimage file format or exploded JDK directories\n- Manages JAR file caching and resource loading\n- Integrates with the SystemDictionary for caching loaded classes\n\n#### SystemDictionary Class Cache\nFile: `src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp` and `systemDictionary.cpp`\n\nThe C++ `SystemDictionary` class (line 78 in .hpp) is the central repository for all loaded classes in the VM:\n- Maintains a concurrent hash table dictionary per ClassLoaderData\n- Stores loaded and initiated classes by class name and loader\n- Provides key methods:\n  - `resolve_or_fail()`: Loads a class or throws exception\n  - `resolve_or_null()`: Loads a class or returns null\n  - `resolve_from_stream()`: Loads a class from a byte stream\n  - `resolve_super_or_fail()`: Resolves superclass with circularity detection\n  - `find_instance_klass()`: Looks up an already-loaded class\n- Uses SystemDictionary_lock for synchronization\n- In systemDictionary.cpp, `compute_java_loaders()` (line 135) initializes the Java-level system and platform loaders\n- Stores references to `java_system_loader()` and `java_platform_loader()` as OopHandles\n\n### Delegation Chain Flow\n\n1. **Application Code**: Calls `ClassLoader.loadClass(\"com.example.MyClass\")`\n2. **AppClassLoader**: Inherits delegation from ClassLoader.loadClass()\n   - Checks cache via findLoadedClass()\n   - Delegates to PlatformClassLoader.loadClass()\n3. **PlatformClassLoader**: Delegates to BootClassLoader.loadClass()\n4. **BootClassLoader**: Has null parent, calls findBootstrapClassOrNull()\n5. **HotSpot Layer**: If not found, class loading continues in native code\n6. **SystemDictionary**: VM caches the loaded Klass object for future lookups\n7. **Return**: Class object returned up the chain to application code\n\nThis hierarchical, parent-first delegation ensures that core classes are always loaded by the bootstrap loader, preventing conflicts and maintaining security boundaries between different trust domains."
}

